text: Semizovac is a village in the Vogošća municipality, near Sarajevo, Sarajevo Canton, Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bosnia and Herzegovina. It is made up of multiple business complexes centred on the infamous Semizovac intersection. ==Population== ===Ethnic composition, 1991 census=== total: 2,130 *Serbs - 1,190 (55.87) *Bosniaks - 699 (32.82%) *"Yugoslavs" - 120 (5.63%) *Croats - 84 (3.94%) *others and unknown - 37 (1.74%) ==History== ==References== *Official results from the book: Ethnic composition of Bosnia- Herzegovina population, by municipalities and settlements, 1991. census, Zavod za statistiku Bosne i Hercegovine - Bilten no.234, Sarajevo 1991.
